Our Practice Areas

At Dean & Camper Injury Lawyers, our local injury attorneys through our five offices in Pensacola, Fort Walton Beach, Crestview, Destin, and Mobile can assist you with your personal injury and wrongful death legal claims.

Car Accidents

Been injured in a car accident? We handle all types of motor vehicle collisions, from fender benders to catastrophic crashes. Our team investigates every detail to build a strong case for maximum compensation.

Learn More About Car Accidents

Truck Accidents

Commercial truck accidents often result in severe injuries. We take on major trucking companies and their insurers, holding them accountable for negligent driving, improper maintenance, and violations of federal regulations.

Learn More

Motorcycle Accidents

Motorcycle riders face unique dangers on the road. When negligent drivers cause accidents, we fight to overcome bias and secure full compensation for your injuries, medical bills, and pain and suffering.

Learn More

Automobile Insurance Claims

Dealing with insurance companies can be frustrating. When insurers deny valid claims or offer unfair settlements, we fight back to ensure you receive the full benefits you're entitled to under your policy.

Learn More

Wrongful Death

Losing a loved one due to someone else's negligence is devastating. We help families seek justice and compensation for funeral expenses, lost income, and the immeasurable loss of companionship.

Learn More About Wrongful Death

Other Personal Injuries

We handle a wide range of personal injury cases beyond auto accidents, including premises liability, defective product claims, and watercraft accidents. Property owners, manufacturers, and boat operators must be held accountable.

Premises Liability

Slip and falls, inadequate security, dangerous property conditions

Learn More
Defective Products

Dangerous or defective products, faulty design, manufacturing defects

Boat and Jet Ski Accidents

Watercraft collisions, negligent operation, boating injuries

Meet Our Attorneys

Experienced trial lawyers dedicated to fighting for injury victims throughout Louisiana.

Shane Dean

Partner & Personal Injury Attorney

Shane Dean has recovered millions of dollars representing victims in personal injury and wrongful death claims resulting from the negligence of others. Selected to the Florida Super Lawyers Rising Stars list for three consecutive years, Mr. Dean is also a member of the Multi-Million Dollar Advocates Forum and recognized as one of the "Premier 100" trial attorneys in Florida by the American Academy of Trial Attorneys.

Mr. Dean obtained his law degree Cum Laude from Indiana University School of Law in 2001, graduating with honors as a Harold R. Woodard Scholarship recipient and member of the Moot Court Team. He is admitted to practice in all Florida and Alabama state courts, as well as the U.S. District Court for the Northern District of Florida and the U.S. 11th Circuit Court of Appeals.

Chad Camper

Partner & Personal Injury Attorney

Chad Camper has recovered millions of dollars for his clients in personal injury and wrongful death claims resulting from the negligence of others. A member of the Million Dollar Advocates Forum (fewer than 1% of U.S. lawyers), Mr. Camper was selected to the Florida Super Lawyers Rising Star list in 2015.

Mr. Camper obtained his undergraduate degree magna cum laude from the University of West Florida and his law degree from West Virginia University in 2006. He began his career at Huddleston Bolen, the top ranked railroad litigation law firm in the United States, defending complex litigation before dedicating his practice exclusively to representing injury victims.

Mr. Camper proudly served five years in the United States Air Force, where he was promoted twice ahead of his peers and received the prestigious John L. Levitow Award, the highest honor in Professional Military Education.
